      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SKINNY HORACE (1) is racing well with 10 top-five finishes in succession, the latest effort a second at Port Pirie over 1609m. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Taking on a better line-up this time but he has the ability to mix it with them. REACT TO BEAUTY (6) had a favourable gate and was too good at this track two runs ago. Drew wide last start and was safely held, beaten 15 metres into ninth at this track over 1800m. It doesn't get any easier but on his best form he is good enough to take this out. SEA HUNTER (2) is the next best after finishing third over 1800m at this track last time out. KEILAH NZ (8) did a good job to finish in the minor placings two runs back then her luck changed last time when she broke and finished a long way back in retired over 1800m at this track. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Beautifully placed and can make amends.",
